entries.femaleVariant: Not feeling well, either?

Not yet.

Who the fuck...?
Keep playin'.
Johnny?
All right. C'mon, tell me – why do you look like a small-time kleptopunk from the Afterlife?

C'mon. Siddown with me, tell me where you've been all this time.

What'll you have?
Sit, please.
Sit the fuck down already.

I mean, got my reputation to think about.
Johnny? You OK?
No.
Ah, so you must be V.

Don't worry about a thing.
The hell is this concert thing?
D'you hear that?
Gets sharper as the pills wear off. So?

Somethin's gotta justify this level of tacky.

Always ate out, always.
Like a fangirl or somethin'?

Motherfucker.

entries.femaleVariant: You look good.
Yeah. What about you?
Not lookin' all bad yourself, either.

Shit, with Arasaka.
Mornings I record at their studio, then evenings Yori pops over for a little neighborly cookout.
Mh, and who'd you really sign with?
MSM Records.
Another pillar of society.

'Cause if I hear you spent them with the nomads, open road, wind in your hair…
Or cool and relaxed in orbit… And now you've just popped by to shit all over my life, well, I'ma lose my damn mind.
Still in touch with the rest of the band?
Depression stuff – is it true?
Never got what Denny saw in Henry.
Stuff about you bein' depressed – it true?
Nope. Promo stratagem.
Suicide attempts, too? Think putting a bullet through your skull'll help your sales?
Didn't work for you. Nobody remembers Samurai.
Seems those were good times, in hindsight.
Never did get what Denny saw in that guy.
Lookin' at 'em now, those really were the best of times.
Still in touch with the gang?
Played fucking rat-infested dumps, argued before every gig…
Had no idea what we wanted to play. And never had an ed to our name.
Nancy – control freak. Henry smelled like zappers 'n' piss. I was always stealin' your pants.
Hella good times, man.
Now you're just butthurt 'cause I managed fine without ya.
I mean, smart imp, that one. Maybe too smart for the company she kept.
Nah, Denny always went for losers incapable of dressing themselves.
Hank was perfect. Half a brain and high all the time – she got to rescue him over and over again.
Why'd she never try and fix me?
Woulda had to get in line, that's why.
Fuck me. Got no answer to that.
Just Nance. Changed her name to Bes Isis, works for N54 News.
Could track down Denny and Henry if you want.
Maybe get together? You know, jam or somethin'.
How is she in general, besides having nothing to do with music?
Could ask her yourself.
Few calls and I should be able to track him down.
Denny might still be in the biz. Actually had talent – and a spine.
Yeah, released somethin' not too long ago. Moved to North Oak, too.
You ever leave this house?
Nope.
Denny should still be playing.
You just said you weren't in touch.
Didn't hear it from her. Think she might be avoiding me.
OK. Let's do it.
All right. Let's do it.
But I'm not gonna have to explain all this again, am I?
But I won't have to explain what happened, all this?
Nah, we'll spare 'em. Hella boring story.
We'll just say you're my new output.
entries.maleVariant: We'll just say you're my new input.

entries.femaleVariant: Biochips, Arasaka's evil schemes, magic pills…
OK, send ya Nancy's number in a sec. I'll go after Henry and Denny.
How'm I--
You two have a good time?
Hang on. You look like shit.
Nah, I'll be fine.
You two have fun at least?
I'll be fine.
Heheh – that a hint of disapproval I hear?
Just sit tight for a bit, rest.
Let's go, V. He's joking.
Callin' from Kerry Eurodyne's residence.
When will she be back?
Callin' from Kerry Eurodyne's residence.
Know when she'll be back?
entries.maleVariant: You know when she'll be back?

entries.femaleVariant: Cool. But Bes still isn't here.
She was s'posed to be back two days ago.
Went to the Totentanz to shoot some stuff, story on Maelstrom.
Call back next week, or just watch the news.
Anything happens to her, I'll be the first to cover it.
Think we better head to the Totentanz.
Axe like that run us many eddies?
Forget it, we couldn't afford it.
That's Kerry's fave.
Wicked bad collection.
"Never Fade Away..."
Guess if I had a fave, it'd be that one.
What's this?
Old single we put out. No idea why Kerry hoards shit like that.
OK, even I know that one.
"Second Conflict."

Guess nothing's changed.
Who's that?
Louise. The ex-wife.

Eehh, too long. But don't worry, it worked out well... for her.
Gave 'er my house in Tokyo, cars, kids… yeah.
Worked out pretty well for you, too, then.
Now, let's see which're up for show and which're actually strummable.
The hell's this freak tech?

Huscle bots. Been here before.

You ever gonna make up your damn mind?

[Play "Chippin' In"]
[Play "Never Fade Away"]
[Play "Archangel"]
Well?
Play.
Forgot what comes next?
[Stand] This is V.
[Stand] Cool, I'll talk to Nancy.
[Stand] Cool, I'll call Nancy.
OK. Callin' Nancy.
[Stand] And you tell me what happened to your throat.
Long as you tell me whatcha got in your throat.
Always did complain I couldn't carry a tune.
We lost everything...
The desire to destroy...
C-can you feel it…
The fuck? I mean – how?
Kerry?
No, no, no, this's some fuckin' joke. Hang on…
What'd Silverhand tell me before he died?
Told you to stop bein' a pussy.
Told you to leave Samurai, go your own way.
Testing me?
This a test?
Could just play you another song.
Answer me.
I told ya to stop bein' a pussy.
Told you to leave Samurai, go your own way.
Johnny fuckin' Silverhand...
Did you? Huh?
Clearly, I was right. As I often am.
Played enough. You know who I am.
[Keep playing] OK.
Played enough. You know who I am.
All right.
What if we get another Rogue situation?
What if this ends up like the Rogue thing – one big let-down?
So far, comebacks don't seem to be workin' out for you.
Nah, this is different. Kerry needs this concert.
Mhm. I'm not there, figure it out with V.
Sure, uh... you two get along?
Sure. Kid loves me.
Not lately, no.
Yeah, I bet.
We don't have much of a choice, though.
Fuck, yeah!
Live here all by your lonesome?
Nah. Got my cook, Ariel – but he's off today, Miguel--
What'm I--? Not your biz, choom. Siddown, start talkin'.
An oldie but a goodie.
[Take glass] Won't be a dry eye in the house.
[Take glass] See for yourself.
Listen, judge for yourself.
Ah, beautiful butterfly Kerry emerging from his silky Samurai chrysalis.
Whoa! It's, like, symbolic.
All right, I'll give him that one.
Bet he sits here and thinks – the fuck I need all this shit for?
Prolly the only actual necessity in this whole pad.
You live alone?
"Never Fade Away..."
What's this?
Rings a bell, that one.
What's this?
How much for that axe?
Uuh, Johnny?
Hellooo, fuckin' Earth to fuckin' Johnny Silverhand.

Preem collection.
